title: My Man Jeeves
creator: P. G. Wodehouse
description: Librivox recording of My Man Jeeves by P. G. Wodehouse. Read by Mark Nelson Bertram Wooster is an English gentleman living in New York, who seems to get himself into all sorts of jams. It's up to his manservant Jeeves to come up with the plan to save the day from unpleasant houseguests, stingy uncles, broken hearts, and hard-partying aunts. (Summary by Mark Nelson) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audiobooks, or to become a volunteer reader, please visit librivox.org. Download M4B (143MB)
subject: librivox; audiobook; literature; Jeeves ; Wodehouse
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: excellent reader and of course wodehouse

Jeeves is an extremely intelligent man who happens also to work as a butler for a, shall we say, not quite as bright young man.  The misadventures they get into are a riot, along with the ingenious solutions Jeeves comes up with to get them out.  This will be a new favorite.  Enjoy!
The Jeeves stories are classics and terribly funny. I adore Mark Nelson's recordings of them. His accent is American, but his tone of amiable naivety is perfect for Bertie Wooster's narration.
reviews.reviewtitle: Great book, great recording if you don't mind the accent

reviews.reviewbody: Seriously, Mark's read of this is great, and the work is a comedy classic.
reviews.reviewtitle: Amazing that he can do such a good Bertie with an American accent.
